activities.message:
@haquaman It seems to me that the check against `MRB_INT_MAX` is only there because the array is indexed by an `mrb_int`, not because the allocated memory size needs to be less than `MRB_INT_MAX`.

Most of the other malloc / realloc calls are already using a `size_t` but I did just notice that this one is using an `mrb_int`, so it likely needs to be patched: https://github.com/mruby/mruby/blob/8461a31cb491f272524d14a9e54fcc9fae7a22c1/src/array.c#L124-L128

I'll check into that and open a second pull request if appropriate.
